+### 12.1 Why This Audit Points Beyond One Noun
+
+Section 2.2 already shows the limit of the old mnemonic: "Telemetry emission" fits only by leaning
+on `Policy::decide(&[], ctx)`, and that awkward-but-functional boundary is exactly what you expect
+when a live transport medium is being squeezed into a durable-record abstraction. Section 3.2
+adds the other half of the diagnosis: the `roko-conductor` → `roko-learn` dependency violation is
+the architectural symptom you get when Bus concerns are not named as first-class. Taken together,
+those two sections motivate the two-medium / two-fabric reframing that REF02-REF05 and REF07
+develop in detail.
